SIMPLE: productive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Productive
<hw>Pro*duc"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>productif</ets>, L. <ets>productivus</ets> fit for
prolongation.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the quality or power of producing; yielding
or furnishing results; <as>as, <ex>productive</ex> soil;
<ex>productive</ex> enterprises; <ex>productive</ex> labor, that which
increases the number or amount of products.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bringing into being; causing to exist; producing;
originative; <as>as, an age <ex>productive</ex> of great men; a spirit
<ex>productive</ex> of heroic achievements.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And kindle with thy own <qex>productive</qex> fire.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is turning nobility into a principle of virtue, and making it
<qex>productive</qex> of merit.</q> <rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Producing, or able to produce, in large measure;
fertile; profitable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pro*duc"tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pro*duc"tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Productivity</ent>⟦br⟧
